																		Author Post -- HUB
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/greenwolf" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1814684); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1814684&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610203537" alt="GreenWolf" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1814684)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/greenwolf" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1814684); return false;" >GreenWolf</a></span> <span class="odate time_1555301379 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">15 Apr 2019 04:09</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4219341">
									

<blockquote>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Lying at my feet I see the offering you bring<br />
The mark of Cain is on our faces, borne of suffering<br />
O, I long to hear you say it's not been wrong<br />
I stand before you now, a riddle in my song<br />
The answer is that sweet refrain<br />
Unheard it always will remain<br />
Beyond our reach, beyond our gain</em></p>
<p><span style="margin-left: 50%">Kansas &#8212; &quot;<a href="https://youtu.be/CUzO9dzEdJ4">The Pinnacle</a>&quot;</span></p>
</blockquote>
<p>This one's a few hours early, but it's Monday somewhere in the world. Here's the hub for this series, along with a little epilogue &#8212; Pietrykau's comments will start making a lot more sense as the remaining tales arrive, trust me. Now that the hub's up, the title of this series has also been revealed, continuing on with the well established bird motif of Third Law and Twisted Pines. If you haven't already figured out who the Phoenix, Nightingale, and Magpies are, you will soon. Probably.</p>
<p>HUGE thanks to <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/crashington" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5028224); return false;">Crashington</a></span> (art page <a href="/crash-s-flashy-art-dash">here</a>) for the art used in the header (and throughout the series). As a work done on commission for this site, it automatically falls under CC-BY-SA 3.0. The rest of the header is my own work, and is also under CC-BY-SA 3.0. The font used for the text in the header is <a href="https://fonts.google.com/specimen/Rock+Salt">Rock Salt</a>, which is available under the Apache License, Version 2.0.</p>
<p>Here's a close-up of the art in the logo: <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/local--files/florence-thorne-hub/2grey.png">Link</a></p>
<p>Crit credits go out to:</p>
<ul>
<li><span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/a-random-day" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1841781); return false;">A Random Day</a></span> &#8212; <a href="/moonlighting">Moonlighting</a></li>
<li><span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jacob-conwell" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1372582); return false;">Jacob Conwell</a></span> &#8212; <a href="/scp-4560">SCP-4560</a></li>
<li><span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tawny0" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2244665); return false;">tawny0</a></span></li>
</ul>
<p>Here's a tentative schedule for the rest of this series:</p>
<ul>
<li><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">Part 5 &#8212; April 17</span></li>
<li><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">Part 6 &#8212; April 19</span></li>
<li><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">Part 7 &#8212; April 22</span></li>
<li><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">Part 8 &#8212; April 26</span></li>
<li>Part 9 &#8212; <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">April 29</span> May 2</li>
</ul>

							</div>

								
